Description: The guitar is in excellent condition for it's age. Includes original "duckfoot" tweed case and an assortment of original case candy. Everything is stock with the exception of the original 3 way switch being swapped out for the included 5 way switch. The original pickup covers have yellowed with age and have been replaced with new white covers to match the rest of the guitar. Original covers and switch are included. Neck is stamped by current Custom Shop builder John Cruz. Very little fret wear on the neck. Truss rod functions fine. Cosmetically there is some chipping of the finish around the neck plate and one small ding on the side of the guitar. There is also a small scuff on the side of the headstock. The volume and tone knobs have some wear from use. The backplate also has a small hairline crack in it. The bridge and tuners have some light oxidation on them as well. The guitar weighs 8 lbs. The pickup readings are as follows: Br/M/Nk 5.53/5.51/5.78K. I only accept PayPal and will only ship within the US. Please send me a message with any additional questions. Thanks!
